### Step 2 — Template detection
Add inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` **after** the Ministral check (~line 1644) and **before** the GPT-OSS check:

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] but no [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

The absence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is the critical distinguisher from the existing Ministral 3 handler.
